import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['life_expect'], data['fertility'])
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    grouped_data = data.groupby('year')['pop'].sum().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(grouped_data['year'], grouped_data['pop'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend in population growth over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    life_expectancy = data['life_expect']
    plt.hist(life_expectancy, bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    data.boxplot(column='pop', by='cluster', ax=ax)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("How does the population of countries vary across clusters?")
    plt.suptitle("")
    plt.xlabel("Cluster")
    plt.ylabel("Population")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Group by cluster and calculate the average fertility rate
    avg_fertility_by_cluster = data.groupby('cluster')['fertility'].mean()
    
    # Create a bar chart
    avg_fertility_by_cluster.plot(kind='bar', rot=0)
    
    # Set title and labels
    plt.title("What is the average fertility rate of countries in each cluster?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Cluster")
    plt.ylabel("Average Fertility Rate")
    
    # Set x-axis ticks if necessary
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
